	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Mar 22nd 6:45 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have all but abandoned my Wizzy and I'm happy to say that I'm happy with my decision. That doesnt mean that I wont, on occasion, use my Wizzy to GG a friend or to make some quick bucks, but for the most part she is retired, and I'm comfortable with that. Anyway, I have some questions concerning play as a Shaman and I hope that I will again get some good advice as I did with my first post. So here it goes: In what situation is the spell Invigor best used? I know it restores fatigue but I'm not really sure when to use it. Does it help you recover lost points on the yellow bar? Doesnt that bar register fatigue? Please correct me if I'm wrong. Also, I've heard some contradictions concerning the use of Spirit of Cheetah. Some say it is nothing but a bother and ineffective, while others swear by it. I would appreciate added input on this subject. Since I never mentioned it, I will mention now that my Shaman's name is Prealia, but I'm logged as Preal, which is my Wizzies name. I dont know if anyone cares but I thought I would offer up the info anyway. I love the fact that Shamans are versatile. I almost died from boredom playing my Wizzy because I'm not a fan of repe<br>tition. I&nbsp;&nbsp;havent discovered any such flaws as of yet with my Shaman. I'll keep my fingers crossed in the hopes that none will arise. As a fellow Shaman has asked me, I'm going to ask those of you who read my posts, please rate my posts so I can have some basic idea of whether or not my posts are having any impact. I dont feel qualified, at this point in my career, to hand out any advice to those younger than myself, but in the future I hope to help those who have come after me just as those who came before me have helped and are still helping me. As more and more unanswered queries occur to me, I will post more and more often in the hopes of salvation. :o)<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
