	   <tr><td colspan=2>If you are kiting STOP!<br>Kitting dose nothing to improve your most important skills (Abjuration, Alteration, Conguration and Melee).&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>Kitting is a limited concept.  There are a limited number of zones where you can kite, and there are a limited mumber of mobs that can be kited.  <br><br>If you solo using the abilites of your shaman you will be albe to solo inside or outside.  You will have far more choices of were to hunt and you will be able to go after some nice items that are not normaly camped by groups.  <br><br>Your most important new spells are: Envenomed Breath, Regeneration, and Cannibalize.  From this point on Dots will start to replace DD as your attack spell of choice.  Regeneration will give you staying power in combat.  Frost strike is a nice upgrade, but for the first few lvl I had difficulty getting it off during combat.  So I would still use Spirit Strike.  <br><br>I recomed you pull the mob with walking sleep, Then cast Afflection and then Envenomed Breath.  <br>Melee the mobs while the dots work.  You may need to recast Envonemed Breath.  Afflection should drop shortly before walking sleep, so when it drops you will need to recast walking sleep or maybe hit the mob with  a dd to finish it off or cause it to run.  You should also be able to cast heal while meleeing.  <br><br>I should of brought this up eairler, Slaming the mob just before you cast, will often prevent your spell from being interupted.  Slam the mob just after it hits you with its main attack, that way you will have maximun time to get your spell off.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
