	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hmmmm.... its all up to you really. <br><br>If you want to be a Wisdom casting shaman (basically all your life you will sit on your arse) and dont mind being KOS to EVERYWHERE in Antonica then go for Iksar. Dump your points into wisdom, strength, and Charisma. My fav thing about iksar is their regen. Proceed with caution on iksar though..... they cant wear plate (except a couple exceptions)<br><br>If you want to be wisdom dependent shaman but not KOS everywhere you go then be a Barbarian shaman. I love their starting area btw. Put points into Wisdom, Cha, and Sta (in order of importance)<br><br>If you want to be a Huge Behemoth and like to get in the fray of the battle every once and a while. And you want to be able to take that mob that aggrod on you when you healed your groupmate, then be an ogre. Ogres arent stunnable in the front, and although they have a lil less wisdom then anyone except the troll there are so many +wis items it really doesnt matter except in the 20's. (high enough where you depend on mana more, but you cant afford better mana and wis equipment)<br>This is my personal Choice (if you know what/where you go at what level then its the BEST newby zone i know of, refer to an earlier post of mine either on this page or ogre page) Make sure to dump all but 5 points into wisdom, then id add that last 5 into charisma. <br><br>Last but definitly not least are the trolls. Arguably the BEST newby area in the game, and the regenning ability make this a great choice. At higher levels with Chloro, your natural regen, a bard healing song, and all the while sitting down you can get HP's back REALLY fast. DO NOT CHOSE TROLLS JUST FOR REGENERATION... iksar have them too. Although trolls dont have the highest stats, they are VERY fun to play. Put ALL points into wisdom. <br><br>When fighting as a low level shaman remember you are basically a SK who got his spells early. You tank, and tank some more. Throwing in a lil blast from burst of flames, and buffing and healing yourself. But you will basicaly melee the mobs to death. Your roll as a caster will shift more to healing and DoT'ing and buffing/debuffing as you get hgiher and higher in level though. By 30 unless you chose a troll or ogre you will ONLY heal and buff and debuff. Being an ogre im the makeshift tank whenever we are low on tanks. You can find level guides for all these races for shaman on the net. So i will leave you with this.<br>ALWAYS be kind to EVERYONE, you never know if that other person is thinking about handing you 100pp just for being nice or not (has happened to me MANY times, i get free stuff all the time just for being funny, nice, and helpful) Also when you get to level 9 the SOw Beggers start. At level 9 and till about 15 the mana it takes to cast it is a lil steep, but by the time you are 20ish its barely noticable. <br><br>Nitsujlak Barshemguud Ogre SHM of War!!<br>Prexus Server<br>Feel free to rate my posts, I love input =)<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
