	   <tr><td colspan=2>Great post Nitsujlak!!<br><br>If you want to be a barbarian shaman:&nbsp;&nbsp;kill all the mobs around everfrost especially polar bears and spiders from lvls 1-5.  Dont fight them in the center of the paths.  Keep yr Str Dex and IF buffs on and pull the mobs out of the way. <br><br> Collect white polar bear pelts and turn them into Cindle at Mac's kilts.  You will receive armor, exp, and gold, I also took up tailoring early on.  By 5th lvl you should have a full set of armor and probably a worn staff and a cracked staff.  Alternate 1h and 2h skills<br><br>Collect wooly spider fungus.  Talk to the man in the corner just outside the guild and he will give u a jar to put the fungus in.  Collect 8 and get spells, exp, and gold.  <br><br>Some players buy the white polar bear pelts for up to 2pp.  Keep that in mind.<br><br>Always buff folks when you start.  It is nice to have a group, you can level quickly.<br><br>After about 6th lvl start to hunt at BB cautiously.<br><br>Always focus on earning money to be able to buy your spells.<br><br>Good Luck, these are just my opinions but they worked for me early on<br><br>Gguril Barbarian Shaman 8th season<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
